For the people of Israel and, I assume the vast majority of the US population, the cause of the conflict has always been the antagonistic spirit existing between the Arabs and the Jews, probably at the root cause because Arab countries were a shore to remain colonized by the European powers. Even the Israelis, who were clearly victims of Arab hostility, offered a post-dividing land so that the Palestinians will dwell alongside, but palestinians refused the deal. It is the post-occupation reasoning that, should palestinians be welcomed with a sense of peace and forgiveness, even the rest of the Arabs would come to peace with Israel’s occupation, and the conflict would be firmly embedded deep beneath Israel’s relations to it’s surroundings but in otherwise peaceful harmony. Very surprisingly, the Palestinians as well as the other Arab people, refused to compromise. Even today, urging the occupying power to recognise its basic political waste would sound like simply settling the score. And this in our time of a phenomenon known as multiculturalism. The Palestinians never accepted PLO’s softening with the Israeli government.
